routeFacts.name: Boston Sprinter
routeFacts.description: Experience the fastest rail line in America, from modern suburbia to sprawling countryside, linking the state capitals of Massachusetts and Rhode Island with Train Sim World 2: Rush Hour - Boston Sprinter. Feel the rush with brand new passengers. As you travel from station-to-station you will see a greater variety in passengers and higher passenger volumes at peak times. All recreating the hustle and bustle of Rush Hour.
routeInfo: The Northeast Corridor: Boston - Providence is a route featuring 49-mile railway between Boston and Providence, with Amtrak ACS-64 and MBTA F40PH-3. This route has the maximum speed of 150mph (with Acela, which is not included), and makes it the railway that has the highest speed limit all over North America. Without Acela, you can still reach 125mph on this route with ACS-64, which is the American route featured in Train Sim World with the highest speed. The route is included in Rush Hour Season Pass.
